Build succeeded. The new installer is at VMA-frontend\dist\Voice Mode Agent Setup 0.1.0.exe.

Two issues were causing the blank screen:

Absolute asset paths — Vite was building with base: "/", so the HTML referenced assets as /assets/.... Inside a custom app:// protocol in a packaged Electron app, these absolute paths didn't resolve correctly. Fixed by setting base: "./" in vite.config.js so paths become relative (./assets/...).

net.fetch with asar paths — The protocol handler used net.fetch(pathToFileURL(...)) to serve files. pathToFileURL creates standard  URLs that don't understand Electron's asar archives, so the packed files couldn't be read. Fixed by replacing it with fs.readFileSync() in electron/main.cjs, which is asar-aware in Electron.

Reinstall from the new .exe and the app should render correctly.
